/* Program to Replace Spaces with Hyphens *\

public class ReplaceSpaces {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "Java Programming Language";
        String result = input.replace(" ", "-"); // Replace spaces with hyphens

        System.out.println("Original String: " + input);
        System.out.println("String after replacing spaces: " + result);
    }
}

Output:
Original String: Java Programming Language
String after replacing spaces: Java-Programming-Language

Explanation:
The replace(" ", "-") method replaces every space character (" ") with a hyphen ("-").
